  + [stability_observation] is best-window sequence switches frequently for most sampled x, while x=200 is a local stable sharp case rather than a general rule
  + [bridge_result] is the atlas does not justify another explicit/Euler bridge as a single coupled identity track
  + [next_reasonable_coordinate] is zero-height or scale-tied cutoff policy, because counting zero pairs directly ignores the height T of included zeta zeros and may be a poor coordinate for explicit-formula truncation behavior
